# Patterns and Conventions

## General coding

- Language: TypeScript throughout (Nuxt 4, server, services, tests)
- Keep changes scoped; prefer existing idioms in nearby files
- Follow lint rules via pnpm lint and ESLint configs in app/eslint.config.mjs

## File naming and routing

- Nuxt pages: app/pages/*.vue with route params in square brackets
- Nitro API: app/server/api/<name>.<method>.ts or nested directories; example: account-register.post.ts, reoccurrence.delete.ts, reports/categories.get.ts
- Admin endpoints under app/server/api/admin/*
- Task endpoints under app/server/api/tasks/*
- Webhooks under app/server/api/webhook/*
- Health routes: app/server/routes/health/

## Server patterns

- Use server/clients/prismaClient.ts to obtain Prisma client (centralized extension/wrapping)
- Validate env eagerly with app/server/envSchema.ts and consume via app/server/env.ts
- Common helpers:
  - withErrorHandler.ts and handleApiError.ts for consistent error mapping
  - accountAccess.ts, accountMembership.ts, requireAdmin.ts for authorization patterns
  - sessionUserProfile.ts, getUser.ts, completeLogin.ts for auth/session management
  - recordAdminAudit.ts, recordIntegrationJobLog.ts, plaidWebhook.ts utilities
  - rateLimitRedis.ts for Redis-based rate limiting (when used)
- Responses: Nitro event handlers return JSON serializable objects; errors standardized via handleApiError

## Input validation

- Use app/schema/zod.ts and related modules to validate payloads where applicable
- Server/env uses Zod to enforce presence/shape of environment variables

## Database and Prisma

- Primary schema in app/prisma/schema.prisma
- Apply schema changes via SQL migrations under app/prisma/migrations/*
- After editing the schema, run prisma generate (CI ensures this in tests)
- Field-level encryption via prisma-field-encryption; encrypted columns annotated with /// @encrypted comments in schema
- Generated re-encryption code in app/prisma/reencrypt/* — do not hand-edit generated files

## Queues and cron

- BullMQ queues live under app/server/queues/*; configure queue names and processors there
- nuxt-cron schedules periodic jobs (app/server/cron/*). Keep jobs idempotent
- Prefer pushing work to queues from API handlers rather than long blocking tasks

## Forecast engine

- Composition under app/server/services/forecast/*
- Orchestrator (ForecastEngine) calls DataLoaderService, AccountRegisterService, ReoccurrenceService, RegisterEntryService, LoanCalculatorService, TransferService, DataPersisterService
- Use ModernCacheService for in-memory caching; unit and integration tests cover behavior extensively

## Frontend

- Use composables (app/composables/*) for API calls and shared UI logic
- Pinia stores in app/stores/*
- Tailwind CSS classes co-exist with @nuxt/ui

## Testing

- Vitest: unit/integration lives alongside features (e.g., server/api/__tests__, server/services/__tests__)
- Playwright: app/tests/e2e/* with snapshots under spec.ts-snapshots/
- Forecast dedicated runner and suites via package scripts
- Set TZ=UTC consistently for deterministic tests

## Security and secrets

- Never commit .env files; pre-commit hook blocks this (.pre-commit-config.yaml)
- TruffleHog enhanced scanner runs in pre-commit
- JWT and RSA services under app/server/services; MFA logic in app/server/lib/mfa.ts
- Use prisma-field-encryption keys (DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY, DB_DECRYPTION_KEY_*) only via env; do not log secrets

## Safe change workflow

- For Prisma changes: add migration, run prisma generate, update tests/seed as needed
- For API changes: update Zod schemas, write/adjust server/api/__tests__ coverage
- For forecast changes: run test:forecast:unit, test:forecast:integration, and full forecast runner
- For queues/cron: ensure idempotence and add unit coverage; keep handler execution bounded
- For encrypted fields: if placeholders/re-encryption are needed locally, refer to scripts/reset-encrypted-users-after-restore.ts and docs/post-restore-encryption-plan.md

## Naming

- Branch names: feat/*, fix/*, docs/* — see CONTRIBUTING.md
- Commit messages: conventional preferred (feat:, fix:, chore:, etc.)
- API filenames: <resource>.<method>.ts (get, post, patch, delete) or nested paths

## Cursor/AI specific

- Follow .cursor/rules/*.mdc, especially 00-global-safety.mdc (do not run builds/servers without being asked)
- Skills for branching/PR/push exist under .cursor/skills/*

